      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE MARKETS: COMMODITIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Silver declines 2.9 percent, to six-month low; July contracts fall 15 cents an ounce, to $5.105; graph; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>SILVER FALLS 2.9 PERCENT. Silver fell to a six-month low, weakening on fear that the dollar's surge will diminish demand for silver and other precious metals priced in dollars. July contracts fell 15 cents an ounce, to $5.105.</p>
      </block>
